#Ad  Here’s my hearty, rich and flavorful Thai Coconut Chickpea Curry. Loaded with warm spices, vegetables and broth, it's perfect for the holidays and ideal for sharing!

Campbell’s® Thai Chicken broth is the base to this recipe and a pantry must have. Prepared using quality ingredients and all natural flavours, this broth has 30% less sodium than the regular ready to use chicken broth and it’s also fat free. Campbell’s ® broths are available in a wide variety of exciting flavours. Campbell's® is challenging Canadians to unleash their creativity with the Coast to Coast Challenge. Share a meal from your kitchen using Campbell's® Broth and don't forget to use hashtag #CampbellsCoastoCoast #CampbellCanada @Campbellcanada 

Ingredients:
•1 can of chickpeas, rinsed and drained
•1 tablespoon oil
•1/2 large onion, diced
•2 garlic cloves, minced
•1 tablespoon fresh ginger, grated
•2 tsp of turmeric powder 
•1 tsp of cinnamon
•1 tsp of coriander   
•300 ml Campbell’s® 30% Less Sodium Ready To Use Thai Chicken Broth
•1 can (400 ml) coconut milk
•Scallions thinly sliced 
•1 red bell pepper, chopped
•1 cup of carrots
•1 Thai chilli 

Instructions:
Heat oil in a large pan and sauté onion with turmeric, ginger, cinnamon, coriander and garlic.
Add chickpeas, vegetables and Campbell’s® Thai Chicken Broth. Bring the liquid to a boil and add coconut milk.  
Lower the heat and cover the pan to let the flavours simmer together for about 15 mins.
Season with salt and pepper as desired. Garnish with pomegranate and serve with white rice.

The 'Vivere di Gusto' lifestyle is all about living with style and embracing the Italian attitude of
enjoying life to its fullest. Ruffino believes everyday should be celebrated and the holidays
are no exception.

As a part of my Southern Italian roots, my family celebrates Christmas Eve with the feast of
seven fishes. This typically consists of seven different seafood dishes so I want to share a
classic costal dish perfect for the occasion. Inspired by Ruffino x Massimo Piedimonte here's
a Stuffed Mussels recipe paired with Ruffino's Prosecco DOC - the perfect sparkler to

Crostoli are a sweet holiday tradition in my family. Light and flaky Italian pastries fried to a golden crisp and dusted with powdered sugar. This year, I was inspired by Ruffino x Massimo Piedimonte to add some extra 'dolce' with panna di cioccolata bianca (white chocolate cream). Served on a small plate along side a glass of Ruffino's Prosecco DOC,
what's not to love! The clean fruity aromas and intense flavors of apples and peaches, pair perfectly with this dessert. #sponsored

I've partnered with Ruffino Canada for another delicious Italian recipe. A twist on the traditional anolini, this pasta is stuffed with a light branzino mousse and served with a decadent Tuscan tomato sauce. Though an unusual pairing for a lighter dish, Ruffino's Toscana IGT Modus— a vibrant blend of Sangiovese, Cabernet Sauvignon, and Merlot—is striking and bold in all the right ways, making it the perfect pairing for this inventive take on anolini. #sponsored

If you don’t feel like baking a classic apple pie, then these Apple Pie Cupcakes are the perfect bite-sized treat! Miniature pies, baked in a muffin pan, with press-in crusts, easy apple pie filling, and a simple crumble topping. Thanks to my @homehardware Mosaic Non-Stick Muffin Pan, Stainless Steel Measuring Cup Set, and Silicone Spatula, these are a breeze to make. Now is the perfect time for making apple pie, so stay tuned for the recipe link in my bio! #hereshow #hhpartner
All-you-can-enjoy brunch🥢 Tell a friend. @kasa_moto

While I love regular pie, there’s something about bite-sized pies that make them so much better -  they're like a slice of heaven in each bite. And let's not forget the Mosaic kitchen essentials from @homehardware that make holiday baking a breeze! It's all about the little things that deliver incredible taste! Check out the recipe below and get ready to impress your taste buds. #HeresHow #HHPartner

 Ingredients: 
•	2 pre-made, ready to roll store-bought pie crusts 
•	2 tablespoons unsalted butter
•	2 large apples, peeled, cored and diced in to 1/4-inch cubes
•	2 tablespoons brown sugar
•	1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
•	1/8 teaspoon salt
•	2 tablespoons lemon juice
Crumble Topping
•	2 tablespoons unsalted butter
•	1/3 cup flour
•	1/3 cup brown sugar
•	1/8 teaspoon salt
•	1 egg for egg wash
•	Whipped cream, ice cream, icing and/or caramel sauce for topping

Instructions: 
1.	Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Lightly spray MOSAIC Non-Stick Muffin Pan with cooking spray.
2.	In a pan, melt butter, add apples, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring often until apples are tender, about 10-12 minutes. Stir in lemon juice and set pan aside to cool.
3.	In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar, butter and mix with the MOSAIC Silicone Spatula until crumbly.
4.	Roll the pie crust out on a floured surface and cut at least 12 circles using a round cookie cutter. 
5.	Carefully press each round into the MOSAIC Non-Stick Muffin Pan. Use your fingers to round the ends into a pie crust. Brush egg wash to the top edges of each cupcake.
6.	Divide the apple filling evenly onto pie crusts in muffin cups then top with the crumble topping.
7.	Bake for 15-20 minutes or until golden around the edges. Remove from oven and let cool. Once cooled, serve the apple pie cupcakes topped with whipped cream, with ice cream, or icing topped with a drizzle of caramel sauce.

Indulge in the magic of the season with this Espresso Bread Pudding drizzled in Bourbon Sauce! Warm, cozy, and completely addicting, it’s the ultimate dessert for the holidays. Plus, @homehardware’s 4-piece set of 6-oz ramekins is a game-changer for both baking and serving in style. Recipe below! @homehardware #HeresHow #HHPartner 

Ingredients: 
•	3 eggs, beaten
•	1 cup white sugar
•	2 tsp vanilla
•	2 tbl brown sugar
•	1 tsp cinnamon
•	1/4 cup butter, melted
•	1 1/2 cups whole milk
•	1 cup heavy cream
•	1/4 cup espresso
•	8-10 croissants, cubed

For the Sauce: 
•	1 cup sugar
•	1 stick butter, melted
•	2 cups heavy cream
•	1/4 cup Bourbon

Instructions: 
1.	Cut day old croissants into cubes. 
2.	Make the custard sauce by beating eggs, whole milk and cream, melted butter, cinnamon, espresso and white and brown sugar. Whisk until fully unified.
3.	Place cubed croissants in a large mixing bowl, then pour the egg mixture over top of the bread, giving it a stir so that all the croissants are evenly covered. 
4.	Spoon into individual ramekins and let sit for 20 minutes before baking. 
5.	Then bake the mixture in your preheated oven at 375F for 35 minutes. 
6.	To make the sauce, combine all the sauce ingredients in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.  Pour over baked bread pudding.
